9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 347, L.D. 528, “An Act to Address the
10 Rise in Rabies in Animals by Appointing Certified Rabies Vaccine Administrators”
11 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 1 and inserting the following:
12 'Sec. 1. 7 MRSA §1808-A, 2nd ¶, as enacted by PL 2001, c. 308, §1, is amended
13 to read:
14 An animal vaccinated against rabies by a person who is not a licensed veterinarian or
15 under the direct, a certified rabies vaccinator appointed and certified pursuant to section
16 3920 or a licensed veterinary technician under the direct supervision or indirect supervision
17 of a licensed veterinarian may not be certified as vaccinated against rabies and must be
18 treated as an unvaccinated animal under Title 22, chapter 251, subchapter 5 and rules
19 adopted pursuant to that chapter. For purposes of this section, "direct supervision" has the
20 same meaning as in Title 32, section 4853, subsection 4-A, "indirect supervision" has the
21 same meaning as in Title 32, section 4853, subsection 4-B; "licensed veterinarian" has the
22 same meaning as in Title 32, section 4853, subsection 5; and "licensed veterinary
23 technician" has the same meaning as in Title 32, section 4853, subsection 11.'
24 Amend the bill in section 4 in §3916 in subsection 1 in the 3rd and 4th lines (page 1,
25 lines 25 and 26 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "or under the supervision of a
26 licensed veterinarian or by a certified rabies vaccinator" and inserting the following: 'or
27 under the supervision of a licensed veterinarian , a licensed veterinary technician under the
28 direct supervision or indirect supervision of a licensed veterinarian or a certified rabies
29 vaccinator'
30 Amend the bill in section 4 in §3916 in subsection 1-A in the 4th and 5th lines (page
31 1, lines 35 and 36 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "or under the supervision of a
32 licensed veterinarian or by a certified rabies vaccinator" and inserting the following: 'or
33 under the supervision of a licensed veterinarian , a licensed veterinary technician under the
34 direct supervision or indirect supervision of a licensed veterinarian or a certified rabies
35 vaccinator'
