COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 347, L.D. 528
1 Amend the bill in section 4 in §3916 in subsection 2 in the 2nd line (page 2, line 4 in
2 L.D.) by striking out the following: "a cat or dog or a certified rabies vaccinator who
3 vaccinates a cat or dog" and inserting the following: 'a cat or dog an animal, a licensed
4 veterinary technician who vaccinates an animal under the direct supervision or indirect
5 supervision of a licensed veterinarian or a certified rabies vaccinator who vaccinates an
6 animal'
7 Amend the bill in section 4 in §3916 in subsection 2-A in the first line (page 2, line 8
8 in L.D.) by inserting after the following: "veterinarian" the following: ', licensed veterinary
9 technician under the direct supervision or indirect supervision of a licensed veterinarian'
10 Amend the bill by inserting after section 4 the following:
11 'Sec. 5. 7 MRSA §3916-A is enacted to read:
12 §3916-A. Definitions
13 As used in this chapter, unless the context otherwise indicates, the following terms
14 have the following meanings.
15 1. Direct supervision. "Direct supervision" has the same meaning as in Title 32,
16 section 4853, subsection 4-A.
17 2. Indirect supervision. "Indirect supervision" has the same meaning as in Title 32,
18 section 4853, subsection 4-B.
19 3. Licensed veterinarian. "Licensed veterinarian" has the same meaning as in Title
20 32, section 4853, subsection 5.
21 4. Licensed veterinary technician. "Licensed veterinary technician" has the same
22 meaning as in Title 32, section 4853, subsection 11.'
23 Amend the bill in section 5 in subsection 1 in the 7th line (page 2, line 39 in L.D.) by
24 inserting after the following: "department" the following: ', a licensed veterinary technician
25 under the direct supervision or indirect supervision of a licensed veterinarian'
26 Amend the bill in section 6 in §3920 in subsection 1 in the 8th line (page 3, line 8 in
27 L.D.) by inserting after the following: "section 3932-A." the following: 'A certified rabies
28 vaccinator must be under the direct supervision or indirect supervision of a licensed
29 veterinarian to administer rabies vaccines to animals.'
30 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 8 and inserting the following:
31 'Sec. 8. 7 MRSA §3923-B, sub-§2-A, as enacted by PL 1999, c. 254, §5, is
32 amended to read:
33 2-A. Rabies tags. An owner or keeper shall ensure that a rabies tag obtained from a
34 veterinarian, a licensed veterinary technician under the direct supervision or indirect
35 supervision of a licensed veterinarian or a certified rabies vaccinator for immunization
36 against rabies is securely attached to a collar of leather, metal or material of comparable
37 strength and that the collar is worn at all times by the dog for which the rabies tag was
38 issued, except as provided in subsection 3. For purposes of this section, "direct
39 supervision" has the same meaning as in Title 32, section 4853, subsection 4-A, "indirect
40 supervision" has the same meaning as in Title 32, section 4853, subsection 4-B; "licensed
41 veterinarian" has the same meaning as in Title 32, section 4853, subsection 5; and "licensed
42 veterinary technician" has the same meaning as in Title 32, section 4853, subsection 11.'
